# CDGI College Event Management System - Implementation Plan

A production-ready MERN stack solution for managing college events at Chameli Devi Group of Institutions (CDGI). This system features 13 interconnected MongoDB models, JWT authentication, QR-based attendance verification, automated PDF certificate generation, and real-time WebSocket notificationsвЂ”all wrapped in a premium glassmorphic UI.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **CDGI Logo Required**: Please provide the CDGI institution logo (PNG/SVG) to be embedded in PDF certificates. Default placeholder will be used otherwise.

> [!WARNING]
> **MongoDB Connection**: Ensure MongoDB is running locally or provide a MongoDB Atlas connection string for the `.env` file.

---

## Architecture Overview

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "Frontend (React + Vite)"
        A[Login/Register] --> B[Role-Based Router]
        B --> C[Admin Dashboard]
        B --> D[Student Dashboard]
        B --> E[Faculty Dashboard]
        C --> F[Analytics Charts]
        C --> G[Event Management]
        D --> H[Event Browser]
        D --> I[Payment Tracker]
        D --> J[QR Code Display]
        E --> K[QR Scanner]
        E --> L[Result Entry]
    end
    
    subgraph "Backend (Node.js + Express)"
        M[JWT Auth Middleware] --> N[Role Guards]
        N --> O[API Controllers]
        O --> P[Services Layer]
        P --> Q[Mongoose Models]
    end
    
    subgraph "Real-time Features"
        R[Socket.io Server]
        S[QR Generator]
        T[PDF Engine]
    end
    
    subgraph "Database (MongoDB)"
        U[(13 Collections)]
    end
    
    O --> R
    O --> S
    O --> T
    Q --> U
```

